Subject: [PATCH 237/285] hwspinlock/omap: support DRA7xx

DRA7XX device family also supports hwspinlocks. The IP
is identical to that of OMAP4/OMAP5, except for the
number of locks. Enable the OMAP hwspinlock driver to be
built if a DRA7xx only config is chosen.

Signed-off-by: Suman Anna <s-anna@ti.com>
[Kevin: The original patch taken from TI
ti-sdk-am437x-evm-07.01.00.00-Linux-x86-Install.bin]
Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/hwspinlock/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/hwspinlock/Kconfig b/drivers/hwspinlock/Kconfig
index 932b8a3..3612cb5 100644
--- a/drivers/hwspinlock/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/hwspinlock/Kconfig
@@ -10,7 +10,7 @@ menu "Hardware Spinlock drivers"
 
 config HWSPINLOCK_OMAP
 	tristate "OMAP Hardware Spinlock device"
-	depends on ARCH_OMAP4 || SOC_OMAP5 || SOC_AM33XX || SOC_AM43XX
+	depends on ARCH_OMAP4 || SOC_OMAP5 || SOC_DRA7XX || SOC_AM33XX || SOC_AM43XX
 	select HWSPINLOCK
 	help
 	  Say y here to support the OMAP Hardware Spinlock device (firstly
